title: What is the first picture in your phone right now? - Quora

response.answer_text: Just took this. Taking a quick break. This is a new condo building. I'm only on the 30th floor currently. I ride 85 floors on the elevator, hop off, walk down every flight of stairs spraying the hand rails and the doors on each floor with disinfectant, carrying and refilling as needed a 5 gallon backpack jug of disinfectant, and then I take lunch and do it again. I was already walking about 15 miles per day plus working out in the park every morning, so this way I get paid $1,100 per week and I get the same amount of exercise as I was not getting paid at all, and I still workout nearly every day at the park. And yes, that is the Empire State Building in the background. I also added one of me just now from the other side of the same floor. Yes, that is Central Park in the background. If I had lots of money and wanted to live in Manhattan, I'd gladly get a condo here. Probably going for like $4–7 million for a small one bedroom though if I had to guess.

I have amassed a shitload of photos! I somehow have almost 10,000 photos!! (That’s the most current photo - a gecko outside my window this morning)  So it goes without saying that I was scrolling for a loooooooooong time to get to the top! I passed by tons of old memories! Old boyfriends, old vacations, and good ol’ times that were had by all. But the very first photo made me smile a mile wide:  It’s my baby Peanut boy, when he was strong and healthy, stretching and showing off how flexible and handsome he was! All my favorite parts of him are here! His white paws that looked like socks. His wonky ‘stupid ear’. The little white spot on his forehead. I miss my Peanut so much, but I was able to think of him and how happy and healthy he was five years ago! That made me smile :-)

I actually saved that picture (on Instagram) because I knew it was a really happy moment for me, and I would want to remember it.  The phone I used to take it was a Galaxy S6. My old phone (LG G2) had a bad battery, and I needed a new phone. I searched for a couple months until the battery got so bad I needed a new phone quickly. I talked with my parents about getting a new one for Christmas, and they agreed. But once I told my dad that the battery was going from 100% to 73% withing 20 minutes while the phone was off, he ordered it right away. It arrived earlier that day I took the picture, but my normal sized sim card wasn't compatible with the nano sim slot. So I waited until after school to go to the AT&T store to get a new nano sim card for $6. The photo was taken after I got the data thing set up. The phone was originally for Verizon (and even says Verizon on the back) but we have an AT&T data plan, which is overpriced as hell. So I had to Google how to actually set up the data with my dad's phone and it worked. Then I took that picture because I liked the sunset in the background. Thus, the first picture I took on my new phone was born.

A lot of crazy things happened in a short span of time in November of 2016. The Cubs won the World Series for the first time in 108 years, and I was an extra on the show CHICAGO JUSTICE that same day. Most of us slept from 2AM-5AM, if at all. My PC broke a few days later, and I have to use a laptop that I despise. On the night I was coming home from CHGO JUSTICE, I thought I had lost my phone, turns out it was hidden in the folds of my trench coat, and about the only thing that made those few days after the Cubs beat the Indians seem more benign was when Donald effing Trump won the election. My phone was under warranty and I had the new one two days later. My main method of transportation to where the main warehouses sets are for the various shows filmed here is the Orange Line elevated train, which starts and stops at Midway Airport. I the airport late in the afternoon for an overnight shoot on THE EXORCIST. As the train made its way northeastward, a Southwest Airlines flight was coming in south for a landing. Here’s the result.

I’ve been working on a huge archiving project to scan thousands (well, as I get into it, tens of thousands) of frames of 35mm film from the days I was really into film photography. Once upon a time, I was such an avid photographer I had a darkroom in my house. Anyway, I have boxes and boxes of 35mm negatives I’m scanning with a film scanner. The negative carrier slipped while I was prescanning this shot, and produced this rather…disturbing image (man, I hate when my face falls off, don’t you?) So I took a photo with my phone.
This is the first picture I took on my new phone -Samsung C7 Pro. I really love how the camera has captured the piercing ray of sunlight. This picture symbolises hope for me.

I only had this phone a few months now, but this is my first photo on this particular one. It's of Ronald Knox, the Grim Reaper from Black Butler. I absolutely love Ronald's outfit, which is of his Moon Awakening. While 99% of people have personal photos on their phone, I just have my interests in the phone. The only exception are a couple Snapchat photos of myself.

Thanks for A2A. What was the first picture you took with your current smartphone? I cannot be 100% certain, but it would most likely have been of a parked motor vehicle. At the time I replaced my phone, I was working in an office in Sydney, and on the very first day that I was 100% responsible for that office, I was rear-ended while stationary in a car-park, inside the company vehicle. A few days later, I had to replace my phone because it died suddenly, and I was in the habit of taking photos of vehicle(s) when I parked them in case I returned to find something amiss. I don’t think of phone cameras as quality cameras, but they’re great for evidential purposes.
